                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>01.</h4>
                            <p>Heat 1 tbsp sunflower oil in a medium saucepan, then soften 1 chopped onion and 2-3 chopped carrots for a few mins. </p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>02.</h4>
                            <p> When soft, turn up the heat, crumble in 500g lamb mince and brown, tipping off any excess fat.</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>03.</h4>
                            <p>Add 2 tbsp tomato purée and a large splash of Worcestershire sauce, then fry for a few mins.</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>04.</h4>
                            <p> Pour over 500ml beef stock, bring to a simmer, then cover and cook for 40 mins, uncovering halfway.</p>
                        </div>
						 <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>05.</h4>
                            <p> Meanwhile, heat the oven to 180C/fan 160C/gas 4, then make the mash. Boil the 900g potato, cut into chunks
							, in salted water for 10-15 mins until tender. Drain, then mash with 85g butter and 3 tbsp milk.</p>
                        </div>
						 <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>06.</h4>
                            <p>Put the mince into an ovenproof dish, top with the mash and ruffle with a fork. The pie can now be chilled and frozen for up to a month. </p>
                        </div>
						 <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>07.</h4>
                            <p>Bake for 20-25 mins until the top is starting to colour and the mince is bubbling through at the edges. (To bake from frozen,
							cook at 160C/fan 140C/gas 3 for 1 hr-1 hr 20 mins until piping hot in the centre. Flash under the grill to brown, if you like.) </p>
                        </div>
						 <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>08.</h4>
                            <p> Leave to stand for 5 mins before serving. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

